# Controller Layer Rules

## Controller Structure
- Controllers must be in controller/ subdirectory
- Use @RestController and @RequestMapping annotations
- Controllers should only coordinate between facade and HTTP layer
- No business logic in controllers, delegate to facades

## HTTP Mapping
- Use appropriate HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Include proper @PathVariable and @RequestParam annotations
- Return ResponseEntity with appropriate HTTP status codes
- Use consistent URL patterns across modules

## Validation and Error Handling
- Validate input using Bean Validation annotations
- Handle exceptions with proper HTTP status codes
- Return consistent error response format
- Include proper CORS configuration if needed

## Documentation
- Use @Operation annotations for OpenAPI documentation
- Include example request/response bodies
- Document all parameters and return types
- Specify possible error scenarios

